data.description:
Love your roomies but really need your OWN SPACE? Want a MOVE-IN READY, up-to-date home? Hate lawn work? Prefer a townhome in a single family home setting? Then this home is for you!

All three Bedrooms have their OWN LEVEL of living quarters to spread out and have complete PRIVACY. You can finally claim your own kingdom! The top two levels have full Bathrooms along with either a Living Room or Family Room (and other rooms too-including a Den!). The nicely FINISHED Basement has a Recreation Room just as large as the common rooms above. The 2nd Level has another hallway Guest Half-Bath to maintain the privacy of your other bathrooms. When you congregate with your loved ones, enjoy the CATHEDRAL ceiling Living Room which is open to the Dining Room AND expansive Kitchen. The Kitchen is perfect for cooking together in style on the espresso QUARTZ COUNTER TOPS. There is plenty of storage for all your Kitchen needs thanks to the plethora of cabinets and two walls of shelves in the pantry closet. There are closets scattered seemingly everywhere in the home with fantastic STORAGE in the shared Storage/Mechanical Room in the Basement.

Techies will appreciate the internet and cable hookups on EVERY LEVEL, in almost every room. White millwork, white 6-panel doors, quartz counters, maple cabinets, vaulted ceilings, aged bronze lighting and fixtures. This home really is UPDATED plus the walls are FRESHLY PAINTED. Upgraded window treatments are NEUTRAL to work with any décor introduced into the home. Location? Perfect. This Tall Grass townhome is CLOSE to every facet of life AMENITIES: shopping, entertainment, restaurants. Association amenities such as the POOL and CLUBHOUSE make this the perfect home for every lifestyle. Oh, and don’t miss the endless WALKING TRAILS that start just around the corner. Call the Listing Broker, Christine Thompson, for a private tour today!
data.whatILove: Big open spaces for family. Very quiet area and the pool is awesome. It feels like you are on vacation. Very quiet, peaceful area. Lots of restaurants / shopping. Schools are great! We are very fortunate to have the pool, tennis courts and walking/biking path in the neighborhood. Right around the corner, past the Fire Station, there’s a movie theater and plenty of restaurants to choose from—as well as shopping.
